== Key Activities and Responsibilities

=== 1. Credit Analysis and Research (60% of time)

*Fundamental Credit Analysis*
- Analyse financial statements (P&L, balance sheet, cash flow) of corporate bond issuers
- Assess creditworthiness through ratio analysis (leverage, interest coverage, liquidity metrics)
- Build financial models projecting future performance under various scenarios
- Compare company performance against sector peers and industry benchmarks
- Evaluate management quality, corporate governance, and strategic positioning

*Sector and Industry Research*
- Monitor macro-economic trends affecting specific sectors (e.g., rising interest rates impacting property developers)
- Track regulatory changes relevant to issuers (e.g., APRA capital requirements for banks, environmental regulations for mining companies)
- Understand sector-specific risks (commodity price exposure, technological disruption, competitive dynamics)
- Maintain detailed sector knowledge bases and update investment theses

*Credit Rating Analysis*
- Interpret rating agency reports (S&P, Moody's, Fitch)
- Develop internal credit ratings that may differ from agency views
- Monitor rating watchlists and anticipate potential upgrades/downgrades
- Assess rating methodologies and identify where the fund's view diverges from agencies

=== 2. Deal Evaluation and New Issue Analysis (20% of time)

*Primary Market Activity*
- Review new bond issuance prospectuses and offering memoranda
- Analyse pricing, structure, and covenants of new issues
- Compare new issues to secondary market alternatives
- Provide investment recommendations to Portfolio Managers on participation
- Attend new issue roadshows and management presentations (for senior analysts)

*Covenant Analysis*
- Review bond documentation including trust deeds and security arrangements
- Assess strength of investor protections (financial covenants, change of control provisions, event of default triggers)
- Identify structural subordination and security package quality
- Monitor covenant compliance for existing portfolio holdings

=== 3. Portfolio Monitoring and Surveillance (15% of time)

*Ongoing Credit Monitoring*
- Track existing portfolio holdings for credit deterioration or improvement
- Review quarterly and annual financial results announcements
- Monitor news flow, ASX announcements, and market intelligence
- Maintain credit watchlists flagging positions requiring closer scrutiny
- Prepare credit review memos when material changes occur

*Early Warning Indicators*
- Track bond price movements and credit spread widening as market signals
- Monitor CDS (Credit Default Swap) spreads where available
- Identify covenant breaches or technical defaults
- Flag refinancing risks and upcoming maturity walls

=== 4. Communication and Collaboration (5% of time)

*Internal Stakeholder Engagement*
- Present credit research and recommendations to Portfolio Managers
- Collaborate with traders on execution strategy and market colour
- Brief risk management on credit exposures and emerging concerns
- Contribute to investment committee discussions and credit forums

*External Engagement* (for senior analysts)
- Attend company management meetings and investor presentations
- Build relationships with corporate treasury teams and investment banks
- Participate in industry conferences and credit forums
- Engage with rating agencies and other market participants

