== Compensation Expectations (Indicative, Australian Market)

=== Base Salary
- *Graduate / Year 1*: \$70,000 - \$85,000
- *Year 2-3*: \$85,000 - \$110,000
- *Year 4-6 (Senior Analyst)*: \$110,000 - \$150,000
- *Portfolio Manager*: \$150,000 - \$300,000+ (varies significantly with seniority and AUM)

=== Bonus Structure
- Discretionary bonuses typical, based on fund performance and individual contribution
- Year 1-2: 10-30% of base
- Senior Analyst: 30-60% of base
- Portfolio Manager: 50-100%+ of base (heavily performance-linked)

=== Total Compensation
- Base + bonus + superannuation
- Long-term incentives (LTI) may be introduced at senior levels, tied to multi-year fund performance

_Note: Compensation varies significantly by firm size, fund performance, and market conditions. Boutique credit funds may offer higher upside but less base security than larger institutional managers._

